text: The abusive father's death.. Oh, that was so satisfying. To watch him burn to death.. It was sweet. But, Milo's video made me squirm, because that's how it really worked. When it comes to the movie.. I liked it. Seeing Bughuul get livid at the end.. Oh damn, he was pissed the fuck off. To me, the movie was good and showed more on how many ways he could get the kids. Music, movies, literature and paintings. He comes through art. The story made sense and there was more of a balance of subtle scares and jumpscares than there was in the 1st movie. Plus, it wasn't as slow as the 1st movie, but there was a build up from start to finish. Milo and the other kids were pretty creepy.. But, I still love the Bughuul
